dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit ran approximately every 2 weeks during CAPS/87 and CAPS/88. If Rs indicated in the unit HAVERP that they have a current romantic partner, the ROMPART unit was administered. In it, Rs are asked how long they have had a romantic relationship with their partner, whether they live with and/or are married to the partner. They then rate the relationship on a number of dimensions, and indicate the extent to which they feel each of nine emotions when with the partner. They rate how attracti ve they think the partner is, how attractive they think they are, and how attractive the partner thinks they are. They also rate how similar they see themselves to be with the partner in terms of personality, attitudes and beliefs, and interests.

The unit was developed by Harry Reis, Bill Ickes, and Deborah Richardson.

No standard scoring.
